e":"Muir","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: topographic name for someone who lived on a moor, from Older Scots <i>muir</i> ‘moor’ (an expanse of bare, wild upland country). There has been some confusion with   Mure  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mure","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): variant of   Morea  .","Scottish: variant of   Muir  .","English: occupational name from Old French <i>muer</i> ‘mewer’, i.e. someone who tended to hawks in the cages in which they were kept while moulting. Compare   Mew  ."]}]},{"name":"Janet","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Jannet","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Janet Muir Heiress of Pokellie was born in 1295, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, her father, Gilchrist Mure of Rowallan and Polkelly, was 26 and her mother, Isabel de Comyn, was 91. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Adam Mure 4th of Rowallan. She died in 1355, in Ayrshire, Scotland, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1295–1355":"1295–1355","1295–1391":"1295–1391","1320–1354":"1320–1354","1325–1399":"1325–1399","1330–1399":"1330–1399","1